The paper deals with constructing a Bayesian graphical model for a database using the relational DB schema. This involves probabilistic dependencies and customized distributions for columns, latent variables, and foreign key links. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DB (Databases). The paper also involves machine learning techniques such as Bayesian graphical models, which suggests the sub-categories cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The scalability of inference on synthetic and real-world data suggests the sub-categories cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
